    "The reduction of optimized sentence pairs makes the Pcc reduce and the MSE increase.",
    "When σ 1 is small, as σ 1 decreases, the sentence pairs those satisfy the recalculation conditions increase.",
    "However, since the adjust- ment of D 1 is for the entire corpus, not necessarily applicable to each sentence (some values of y i are equal to 1 or close to 1), the dimension D 1 after reduction is too small for sentence pairs with a small annotated similarity y i, which makes the semantic deviation between sentence pairs increase by recalculating.The right part of Table 4 illustrates the impact of the relative error threshold λ 1 on the Pcc and MSE.",
    "We convert the constraint functions 16 and 17 asf i (x) = x i -(1 + λ 1)y i = x i -y i -λ 1 y i = R i -λ 1 y i, (20)g i (x) = (1 -λ 1)y i -x i = y i -x i -λ 1 y i = -R i -λ 1 y i, (21)where R i = x iy i denotes the similarity difference R i between the experimental result x i and the annotated result y i.",
